Kiosk-side Alembic migration tree.

The kiosk's local database is SQLite under SQLCipher; migrations are
applied via the env.py here, which builds an engine through
``ginhawa_kiosk.db.session.create_engine_for_kiosk`` so the SQLCipher
PRAGMA key is set on every connection.

Schema discipline:
* The schema source of truth is ``/schema.sql`` at the repo root.
* Every migration here has a counterpart in ``cloud/alembic/`` —
  except migrations that touch tables the kiosk does not have
  (``users``, ``device_credentials``).
* Type substitutions vs the cloud: TEXT → String, REAL → Float,
  INTEGER → Integer.

Usage:
    cd kiosk
    KIOSK_DB_PATH=/path/to/db KIOSK_DB_KEY=... \
        uv run alembic upgrade head
